summary:
Avengers: Houses
Tony: Gryffindor 
Tony was a tough choice and it’s still a draw. He’s a very intelligent man, quite witty, but...
body:
Avengers: Houses

Tony: Gryffindor

Tony was a tough choice and it’s still a draw. He’s a very intelligent man, quite witty, but his personality other than being a condescending know-it-all when it comes to technology would make him a good Ravenclaw but since Harry Potter takes place before most technology and there is barely any in the wizarding world— well, in Hogwarts, I don’t think he would strive as well as he would in the modernized Ravenclaw House.

He is very brave and courageous, there’s no doubt about that. His attitude would fit very well in both Gryffindor or Slytherin. He’s a bit too boisterous for Hufflepuff, he stands out more and would definitely be someone to always make his prescence known to other students. Thus making him look like an ass. I compare his character to the younger, flirtatious Sirius Black or the cocky James Potter.

Thor: Gryffindor

Thor could honestly be in any house. He’s loyal, creative, brave, and can be quite cunning. He’s literally the whole package and as the Sorting Hat reveals, it’s all in what you want to do, where you want to be placed. Thor can see that most of his friends are being placed into Gryffindor, looking like a lively fun-loving bunch and instantly—that’s where he needs to be! Thor is able to get along greatly with everything, his laughter sometimes being so loud that is shakes the castle, lightning and thunder crackling across the sky.

Loki: Slytherin

He is the God of Mischief after all. Oh, how he would thrive in Slytherin. He’d seamlessly walk all over unworthy and snobby rich kids that found their way into Slytherin. He would tell them stories to scare them at night, tricking them and turning into creatures that they could have only seen in their nightmares. When he explained that Thor was his brother, people were shocked by the stark contrast between the two. Thor, loud and lovable and Loki, ever cunning and crafty.

Steve: Hufflepuff

Steve would also do well in Gryffindor but I wanted to avoid sorting every single freaking Avenger into Gryffindor because heroes are born from all walks of life. The traits of the Houses don’t necessarily have to define you to the letter. While yes, Steve would have liked to be with his friends, something also called to him when he saw Hufflepuff and reminded him of before he had the Serum. He was a nobody then, Hufflepuffs don’t seem to get any spotlight, they aren’t noticed as much. Cast aside by the more fierce Houses like Gryffindor and Slytherin. He felt he needed to be in Hufflepuff because it reminded him of how he used to be.

Peter Parker: Gryffindor

Following after Dad Tony would be in Gryffindor. At first he could be similar to Neville Longbottom, shy and hard to break out of his shell. While his school work is alright, he has an exceptional knack for Care for Magical Creatures and he really likes Transfiguration. He thought about really wanting to learn to become an Animagi but the process he had to go through was so lengthy. He wasn’t sure if he could keep up with it. He’d probably be able to turn into a spider, just he luck.

Natasha: Slytherin

She’ll have you figured out before you can glance in her direction. She’ll keep to herself considering Clint and Steve are elsewhere. Hands shoved in the pockets of her robes, she’ll make it seem like she doesn’t care but aces all of her classes anyways and can be found in the library studying most nights.

Clint: Hufflepuff

When the Houses were explained to him on the train, Hufflepuff seemed like the best choice. Sure, he was brave. He was a whole lot of other things too. Like Steve, he thought being sorted into Hufflepuff would be a cheer for the little guy. Gryffindor and Slytherin, and even Ravenclaw, already had so many students. He felt like he could fit in to Hufflepuff better than the overshadowing Houses. Plus his Common Room is right next to the kitchens and so he’ll totally sneak out for a midnight snack.

Bruce: Ravenclaw

Bruce is arguably one of the smartest Avengers and he is always in the pursuit of more knowledge. He’d be the kind of wizard aiming to cure diseases that strike both the wizarding world and the Muggle world. He’ll want to he able to make a difference that matters!
